Text.Value: Don't thank me - I'm breaking Lady Shar's teachings just by doing so... but sometimes you have to be practical.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little embarassed at being thanked

Text.Value: I... yes, she must. I'll offer thanks to her in my prayers - and we should speak more later. Alone, ideally.
Heavens forbid. We're all entitled to our secrets.
Don't make a fuss, Selûnite - we may be at odds, but I have more important concerns than you right now.
Selûne is a bad omen - just look what's befallen her temple.
EXPLAIN.
I bow to Shar also. The Dark Lady must favour us, to have brought us together.
You worship Shar? Blimey. She and my beloved Mystra are not exactly friends.
Shar is an abomination. You deceived me.
If you insist. Don't expect to fare well without me to save you.
Let the matter rest.
Talk to me later. We've got more pressing matters to see to right now.
We can discuss this later. But let's just try a little more honesty going forward.
In future, I expect you to be honest. Let's leave it at that for now.
Not your usual haunt, I take it.

EditorData.logicalname: Non-Selune SH KNOWN AS SHAR FOLLOWER

Text.Value: Selûne, a bad omen? Hardly. What's really the matter?

EditorData.logicalname: Non-Selune Class, SH didn't get a Shar clue

Text.Value: Let's do what we have to, then get out of here.
The goddess of secrets? How telling.
I didn't agree to join up with a Shar worshipper.
I worship Shar, the Mistress of the Night. It is my holy mission to oppose Selûne, her teachings and her followers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not information she ever shares lightly.

Text.Value: Nothing. Merely an observation.

EditorData.NodeContext: Doesn't like this line of questioning, but trying to show it.

Text.Value: I don't know how I feel about this.
I'll decide whether to make a fuss or not. Hard to trust someone who's holding out on me.
You're far too eager to disrespect Selûne - what's going on?

EditorData.logicalname: Selune Class, SH didn't get a Shar clue

Text.Value: Gather your thoughts. Then perhaps we can talk some more.
We don't have time for this. Besides, I already explained myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Doesn't like this line of questioning, but trying to show it.

Text.Value: Let the matter rest.
Now that you have the truth, please don't make a big fuss about it.
A lie of omission at most. I'm sure you have some skeletons of your own hidden away.
Show some respect. This is a sacred place for me... even in its current state.
A ruin abandoned to a murderous horde is a very fitting dedication to Selûne.
You're not going to let this go, are you? You might wish you had...

EditorData.NodeContext: Coming around to telling the truth about herself.

Text.Value: Is your hearing failing you? Or your wits perhaps? There's nothing more to say. Let's move.
Though I'll grant it must have been impressive once, in all its profane glory... until someone razed it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight concession, glancing around an impressive temple

Text.Value: Of course I am. But we can talk about this later - let's go.
I don't care who you worship. We have bigger problems.
Gladly.
Secrecy is everything for Shar's children. It's our code, our creed, our shield.
It's been some time since I met another faithful of Shar. Are you versed in her teachings?
Respect's given freely. If your goddess needs to demand it, she's not worthy of it.
Only that you're overthinking a simple deduction I made.

EditorData.NodeContext: Doesn't like this line of questioning, but trying to show it.

Text.Value: Your blindness as much as my deception, Selûnite. We can talk about this later - if you're willing.
All we can do is try, I suppose...
You seem to admire whoever left this place a ruin. Got something to say?
Then it's your own fault for not asking.
Let's see how open-minded I can be then: tell me more.
Don't make a big fuss...? You've been lying to me!
True. I didn't think you'd react so pragmatically. Perhaps I should have told you sooner.
Now that the truth's out, tell me more.
What's the problem?

EditorData.logicalname: SH NOT KNOWN AS SHAR FOLLOWER

Text.Value: Though perhaps that might change, if you can show an open mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conceding jus a little towards the player's hurt feelings - but conditionally

Text.Value: Good. I wasn't intending to.
A Shar worshipper? Not my usual quarry - nor my usual ally.
Good. Selûne is a bad omen - just look what's befallen her temple.
I'm not sorry I kept this from you. Not one bit.
You don't have to tell me twice.
Thank you for telling me, at least.
I even keep secrets from myself - I had my memories suppressed, so that nothing I knew could be used against the Dark Lady. Once I prove myself, my memories will be restored.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only if the memory suppression beat wasn't established

Text.Value: No matter. I'll breathe easier once we're clear of this place.
Who says you have to feel anything?
Selûne. As if mingling with a horde of goblins wasn't bad enough.
Quite the understatement, but yes. Let's not linger in this place any more than necessary.
I can't trust you. Best if we travel separately for now.
Spare me your dramatics. I already told you all there is to tell. Let's go.
Leave.
Fantastic. Monsters in our minds, and around our campfire.
Forever, ideally. And you assume too much about what I can and cannot tell.
Watch your tongue, Sharran. This is a sacred place for me... even in its current state.
Though I'll grant it must have been impressive once, in all its profane glory... I wonder what happened.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight concession, glancing around an impressive temple

Text.Value: You could have told me. How long were you going to keep this secret?

Synopsis: Shadowheart, enters the inner area of the goblin camp - what was clearly once the central hall of a Temple dedicated to Selûne, the rival of Shadowheart's goddess, Shar. She notes that this must have once been a key area for Selûnite power and wonders what happened here. If she discovered earlier clues, she may believe Sharran allies destroyed this place long ago. The player may or may not be aware of Shadowheart's shar worshop at this point, and can attempt to pry the info from her.
